g.text: We'll be visiting food trucks, supper clubs, cooking classes and workshops too!
Is this limited to only brick and mortar restaurants?
Nope! Despite the name, you don't have to be brown. We're inviting anyone who identifies as a Womxn of Color to join us, no matter your background.
Do you have to be a brown womxn?

text.tspan: but also an index of minority run

g.text: Besides having amazing food, these restaurants are highly underrated and can use our support in a city dominated by systemic racism, gentrification and a general lack of diversity. These places are less likely to get your business compared to restaurants with investors, hospitality groups and PR behind them. These restaurants need your business to survive.
We hold meetups at POC, WOC and immigrant owned restaurants in the greater Austin area.

We're a group of badass Muslim brown gals (hence the name) based in Austin and we like to eat.Some of us are new to Austin and some have been here a while. We were searching for community and found each other. We figured there are other ladies out there hungry for connection, support and good food so we started this club!

Yes! Send us pictures and reviews of any minority owned restaurants you love via DM or email.We'd love to feature them on our page! Please include photos, restaurant name, location, the type of cuisine, price range and general vibe so we can maintain a consistent and detailed index. Credit will be given, but let us know if youâ€™d prefer us not to.
Send it our way! Please DM or email us to submit recommendations to minority owned restaurants in the greater Austin area.
It sucks that you can't make it but feel free to visit any restaurant we highlight on your own. Be sure to tell your friends and family too! We want to drive business to these places.
What if I can't make it but really want to try that place?

Everything! The focus is on POC, WOC and immigrant owned restaurants and the rich culinary cultures behind them. We'll be exploring restaurants and cuisines from all over the world. Bring your curiosity and maybe some Tums.
Meetups will be held monthly! Keep an eye out on our Instagram page for announcements on when and where we're eating.
